### DISCREPANCY 2 — `os.rename` vs `os.replace` (Minor, Documentation vs. Implementation)

**Docs/agent instructions say:** `os.rename` (used in both `stampede-agent.agent.md:242`, `stampede-merger.agent.md:304`, `bin/stampede-merge.sh:504`, and referenced as "`mv`" in SKILL.md, AGENTS.md, copilot-instructions.md)

**`stampede.sh` uses:** `os.replace()` / `Path.replace()` in all three of its atomic helper sites (lines 157, 668, 1018)

`os.replace` is actually the more correct POSIX primitive (guaranteed to atomically overwrite; `os.rename` raises `FileExistsError` on Windows if dest exists). However:
- The docs and agent instructions uniformly say `os.rename`
- Agents following instructions will use `os.rename`, which is fine on Linux/macOS but diverges from what `stampede.sh` models
- SKILL.md Landmine #3 mitigation says "`mv`", which maps to `os.rename` — the shell launcher uses `os.replace` without documenting the upgrade

**Impact:** No runtime bug on POSIX, but agent-authored code (following instructions) and launcher-authored code use different calls with different error semantics on non-POSIX targets.

