   - sq-029 consensus is no code snippet enforcing the order: write-result → remove-claim. If the commander writes the bundle but crashes before removing the claimed file, the monitor will eventually (after 180 s) `mv` the still-present claim back to `queue/`, causing a second commander to re-execute an already-completed task and overwrite the bundle. The worker agent (`stampede-agent.agent.md:251`) uses `rm -f "CLAIMED_DIR/TASK_FILE"` after result write, but commanders have no equivalent enforced snippet.

